notesStmt.note: Textblock in simple case binding with hollow and tiny squares.
Box binding converted to detached outer case. Spine splitting at joints and tears at headcap.
Usage stains, finger grease in margins.
Portions of a Service Book (Psalms) pasted on one of the end flyleaves.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1 2; ruled lines: 15 30; written lines: 15 30; Uniform layout. Larger initial words and chapter titles. Running titles. Catchwords on every page. Visible hard-point ruling. Folio 1 is a title page.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite semi-cursive script of the 18th century.

binding.p: Post-1600. Brown leather, blind tooled case, with clasps.

history.provenance: Acquisition: Weiss & Co.: purchased by the British Museum on 11 April 1908: inscribed, folio [337v].
